Animation in R:
the largest value until the current roll

Junkyu Park

library(gganimate)

# Largest value

## Variables
max_n <- 50
v <- c(1, rep(0, 6))
P <- diag(0:6)
for (i in 1:7) {
    for (j in 1:7) {
        if (i < j) {
            P[i, j] <- 1
        }
    }
}
P <- P / 6

## Visualizing changes in mu

Pn <- function(n, Pn_1) {
    if (!missing(Pn_1)) {
        return(Pn_1 %*% P)
    }
    result <- diag(1, 7)
    for (i in 1:n) {
        result <- result %*% P
    }
    result
}

mu_n <- function(n) {
    v %*% Pn(n)
}

mu_collection <- sapply(1:max_n, mu_n)
mu_collection <- cbind(0:7, mu_collection)
colnames(mu_collection) <- c("eyes", 1:max_n)
mu_collection <- dplyr::as_tibble(mu_collection)

library(tidyr)
mu_collection_tidy <- mu_collection %>%
    gather(key, value, -eyes) %>%
    dplyr::mutate(key = factor(key, levels = 1:max_n))
anim <- mu_collection_tidy %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = factor(eyes), y = value)) +
        geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
        labs(title = "{closest_state}") +
        transition_states(
            key,
            transition_length = 1,
            state_length = 1
        ) +
        enter_fade() +
        exit_fade()

animate(
    anim, fps = 30, duration = 10,
    start_pause = 5,
    end_pause = 5
)
